  { title:'Love Live! / Love Live! Sunshine!!', spots:[
    { place:'Kanda Myojin Shrine', lat:35.7021, lng:139.7709, episode:'Season 1 - Multiple Episodes', time:'Morning', desc:"The iconic shrine where Honoka and the μ's members pray for their group's success. A must-visit spot — the shrine itself sells official Love Live! collaboration goods.", access:'5-minute walk from Akihabara Station (Electric Town Exit), or 8 minutes from Ochanomizu Station' },
    { place:'Myojin Otokozaka Steps', lat:35.7015, lng:139.7698, episode:'Season 1 - Training Scenes', time:'Morning', desc:"The long stone staircase where the μ's girls famously trained by running up and down. Recreating the scene here is a rite of passage for every Love Live! fan.", access:'Adjacent to Kanda Myojin Shrine, 5-minute walk from Akihabara Station' },
    { place:'Akihabara UDX Building', lat:35.7004, lng:139.7735, episode:'Season 1 - UTX High School Scenes', time:'Noon', desc:"This large commercial complex served as the model for UTX High School, the rival school in the anime. The Tokyo Anime Center on the upper floors is a bonus stop for anime fans.", access:'1-minute walk from Akihabara Station (Electric Town Exit)' },
    { place:'Akihabara GAMERS', lat:35.7006, lng:139.7727, episode:'Season 1 - Flyer Distribution Scene', time:'Noon', desc:"The famous multi-floor anime merchandise store where the girls handed out flyers to cure Umi's shyness. Still a go-to spot for Love Live! goods and events.", access:'2-minute walk from Akihabara Station (Electric Town Exit)' },
    { place:'Cure Maid Cafe', lat:35.7003, lng:139.7718, episode:'Season 1 - Kotori Part-Time Job', time:'Afternoon', desc:"The real-life cafe that inspired the maid cafe where Kotori secretly worked as the Legendary Maid Minalinsky. Occasionally holds Love Live! collaboration events.", access:'3-minute walk from Akihabara Station (Electric Town Exit)' },
    { place:'Tokyo Station Marunouchi North Exit', lat:35.6814, lng:139.7671, episode:'Season 2 - Episode 10', time:'Morning', desc:"The iconic red-brick facade of Tokyo Station's north exit, where the μ's members gathered before departing for their training camp.", access:'Directly outside Tokyo Station, Marunouchi North Exit' },
    { place:'JR Numazu Station North Exit', lat:35.1075, lng:138.8634, episode:'Season 1 - Episode 3', time:'Noon', desc:"The gateway to all Aqours pilgrimage spots. The station's north exit walkway is recreated almost exactly in the anime. Look for Love Live! Sunshine!! posters and taxi wraps as soon as you arrive.", access:'Approximately 1 hour from Tokyo by Shinkansen to Mishima, then transfer to local train (15 min)' },
    { place:'Awashima Marine Park', lat:35.0392, lng:138.8614, episode:'Season 1 - Episodes 1-2', time:'Morning', desc:"The aquarium island that appears in the very first episodes of Sunshine!!. Reimagined as a diving center where Kanan works. Mari's helicopter arrival scene was also set here.", access:'From Izu-Nagaoka Station, take the Izu Hakone Bus toward Izu-Mito Sea Paradise, about 25 minutes' },
